OK, I'm NOT going to write about &quot;Cannon Fodder&quot;.  I'm a Vietnam vet (3rd. batt./1st. Marines, 1968 - 1969) who tries to read as much as I can about 'Nam (so far, I've `missed' Cannon Fodder).  I think two of the best I've read so far are Michael Herr's &quot;Dispatches&quot; and Tobias Wolff's &quot;In Pharaoh's Army&quot;.  Tim O'Brien's stuff is good too.  Any other recommendations, for vets and non-vets alike?
